# Production Environment Configuration

## .env.production (Template)

```env
# Application
APP_NAME="Notes of Shahrier"
APP_ENV=production
APP_KEY=base64:YOUR_GENERATED_KEY_HERE
APP_DEBUG=false
APP_URL=https://yourdomain.com

# Localization
APP_LOCALE=en
APP_FALLBACK_LOCALE=en
APP_FAKER_LOCALE=en_US

# Maintenance
APP_MAINTENANCE_DRIVER=file

# Security
BCRYPT_ROUNDS=12

# Logging
LOG_CHANNEL=stack
LOG_STACK=single
LOG_DEPRECATIONS_CHANNEL=null
LOG_LEVEL=error

# Database (Update these!)
DB_CONNECTION=mysql
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=3306
DB_DATABASE=your_cpanel_database_name
DB_USERNAME=your_cpanel_database_user
DB_PASSWORD=your_strong_database_password

# Session
SESSION_DRIVER=database
SESSION_LIFETIME=120
SESSION_ENCRYPT=false
SESSION_PATH=/
SESSION_DOMAIN=null

# Cache & Queue
BROADCAST_CONNECTION=log
FILESYSTEM_DISK=local
QUEUE_CONNECTION=database
CACHE_STORE=database

# Mail (Update with your cPanel email settings)
MAIL_MAILER=smtp
MAIL_HOST=mail.yourdomain.com
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USERNAME=noreply@yourdomain.com
MAIL_PASSWORD=your_email_password
MAIL_ENCRYPTION=tls
MAIL_FROM_ADDRESS="noreply@yourdomain.com"
MAIL_FROM_NAME="${APP_NAME}"

# Vite
VITE_APP_NAME="${APP_NAME}"
```

## Notes

1. **Never use `APP_DEBUG=true` in production!** It exposes sensitive information.

2. **Database Credentials**: Get these from cPanel → MySQL Databases

3. **Email Configuration**: 
   - For cPanel: Use `mail.yourdomain.com` as MAIL_HOST
   - Port 587 for TLS
   - Port 465 for SSL

4. **APP_URL**: Must match your domain (with https://)

5. **SESSION_DOMAIN**: 
   - Leave null for single domain
   - Use `.yourdomain.com` for subdomains

## Security Best Practices

✅ Use strong database passwords
✅ Keep APP_KEY secret
✅ Use HTTPS/SSL certificate
✅ Set proper file permissions
✅ Never commit .env to version control
✅ Regularly update dependencies
✅ Monitor error logs
✅ Use database backups
